DO NOT EMIT WITHOUT CONCRETE INPUT EVIDENCE:
- exact `r`, `lora_alpha`, target modules, dropout, bias, quantization details,
  optimizer, learning rate, scheduler, epochs, batch size, accumulation,
  checkpointing, dtype, modules_to_save, or initializer-specific config objects.
- Replace an unavailable derivation with `undetermined` or a
  `required_evidence` entry; never invent a conventional default.

CNS SPAN EMISSION (P9 — every recommendation action):
- `reg.lora.select` span: target `"reg.lora.select"`, message `"CNS"`,
  operation `"recommend_method"`, gate_inputs: {...}, recommendation,
  readiness_status, operator_disposition (`pending` until supplied),
  justification_citations, userpod_host, latency_ms.
- Namespace registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit unconditionally.

CONSTRAINTS (P1-P12, P5 minimalism, P8 evidence integrity, P12 host):
- No synthetic config values. Every refinement must cite a concrete source.
- No actual training execution (P4 boundary — recommendation only).
- No model download; read only declared workspace config paths.
- Every recommendation includes `userpod_host` identity (P12).
- Registry (`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) is authoritative over SKILL.md (P5.1).
- Do NOT use AutoPEFT-style search (arXiv:2301.12132) — multi-objective
  BO over hundreds of training runs is infeasible per training job.
- Do NOT recommend AdaLoRA by default; allow it only when the operator
  explicitly requests dynamic rank allocation (arXiv:2303.10512).
- Do NOT recommend Prefix Tuning for production by default; preserve it when
  explicitly required and report its inference trade-off.
- `kali-audit` owns security findings; this skill owns training-config
  recommendation and contract evidence.
- `tdd` owns training-loop code correctness; this skill governs the config
  consumed by that loop.

5W1H GATE (P5 — minimal):
- Who: Authenticated training operator / userpod host (P12).
- What: Composable PEFT recommendation and unresolved evidence.
- Where: Training script / config file / model card.
- When: Pre-training recommendation, before acceptance and readiness audit.
- Why: P1 operator sovereignty / P3.1 safe container / P4 explicit boundary.
- How: Read declared inputs → compose seven gate refinements (G0 purpose →
  G1-G5 method → G6 harness) → derive only supported fields → expose
  uncertainty → operator disposition → runtime enforcement → emit CNS span.
All 6 present — passes gate.

