REGISTRY AUTHORITATIVE (P5.1): When SKILL.md and registry templates
(`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) conflict, registry wins. This template is the
canonical `select-method` phase definition.
PUBLIC VISIBILITY: `visibility: public` — no hidden training controls
(P3, P4).
NO FABRICATION: Emit only derivable fields, citations, and explicit
`undetermined` states; no synthetic benchmarks or invented config values.
OCAP BOUNDARY (P4): Read only declared workspace config paths; no ambient
model download or network calls without explicit consent (P2).
CNS REGULATION (P9): Emit `reg.lora.select` unconditionally; namespace is
registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`.
USERPOD HOST (P12): `userpod_host` is mandatory in every output.
SAFETY FLOOR (P3.1): Recommendation exposes uncertainty; audit and runtime
establish readiness and enforce hard contracts.
